                "citation_count": 2,
                "reference_count": 0,
                "abstract": "\n A model for the computation of energy dissipation in transient flow is presented in this paper. The energy dissipation is used to define a non dimensional parameter that modifies the friction term in the governing equations and allows the computation of unsteady friction losses. A comparison of measured and computed pressure heads for laminar and turbulent flow cases are presented.",
